&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re making an investment in the next generation of veterinary doctors!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the professional veterinary curriculum, colleges encourage off-campus educational experiences in practices outside of the teaching hospital. Practical experience in a well-run and contemporary practice can be a valuable component of your veterinary education, preparing you to deliver better care after graduation. Our program is dedicated to contributing to your practice-readiness and to help you hit the ground running after graduation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our program structure:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our externships are flexible—they can range from two to eight weeks during the year, according to your college curriculum – but are typically two or three weeks in length.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our externship rotations are designed to allow students, under veterinary supervision, to practice the problem-solving, technical and communication skills that they have acquired during their clinical preparation. Externs are given the opportunity to work alongside our veterinary team and are encouraged to participate in all aspects of patient care. A stipend of $250 per week will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Externs experience the typical caseload of a small animal practice. Under the supervision of your mentor doctor you will gather histories, perform physical examinations, develop diagnostic and therapeutic plans, scrub in to surgery, assist in the management of medical cases, provide wellness care, develop your client communication skills, polish your technical skills and produce appropriate medical records (SOAPs) within the time limits of daily practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we&#39;re looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Extern students are expected to be enthusiastic and effective participants in our patient care activities, upholding the professional and ethical standards of our practice. Students participating in the externship program are suggested to review the Veterinary Practice Act in regard to the scope of duties that may be performed, and to be familiar with the type and degree of veterinary supervision that is required. These should be followed carefully in order to protect both yourself and our practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a veterinary student extern, we expect you to dress and behave in a professional manner and to meet the expectations that we have of all team members as outlined in our employee handbook.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be enrolled in an accredited DVM program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are authorized to work in the United States.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must carry professional liability insurance. AVMA PLIT liability insurance is free for all student members of the AVMA. You may apply for this coverage on their &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.avmaplit.com/products/student-liability/&quot;&gt;website&lt;/a&gt;. Please check to make sure your coverage is current and submit a certificate of coverage with your application.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As sponsors of the Veterinary Externship Program, we see ourselves to be part of your educational team, providing instruction, mentoring and evaluation of the students who participate. You will be assigned a mentor and work on the learning objectives as defined by your college program or to meet your specific goals. At the end of the externship your mentor will provide a written evaluation of your performance as required by your college program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to working with you!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.maplewood.vet/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maplewood Veterinary Center&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;part-time or full-time Veterinarian&lt;/strong&gt; to join our growing practice in Bettendorf, IA, along the mighty Mississippi River!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Address:&lt;/strong&gt; 4269 53&lt;sup&gt;rd&lt;/sup&gt; Avenue, Bettendorf, IA 52722&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What to Expect:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt; base salary of $120,000 - $140,000 per year &lt;em&gt;plus&lt;/em&gt; production (no negative accrual)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonuses:&lt;/strong&gt; up to $50,000*&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule: &lt;/strong&gt;open to part-time or full-time&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours of Operation:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monday – Friday: 7:30 AM - 5:00 PM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Saturday &amp;amp; Sunday: Closed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maplewood Veterinary Center is a full-service small animal general practice serving Bettendorf, IA, and the surrounding Quad Cities community along the Mississippi River. We provide comprehensive daytime care in general practice, surgery, and dentistry. Our team embraces the philosophy of “treat others as you would like to be treated” and values the human-animal bond at the heart of everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a member of our team, you can expect to be supported in your work and personal life with:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work/Life Balance.&lt;/strong&gt; We know your life outside of work is just as important. That’s why we offer flexible scheduling options—whether you&#39;re looking for full-time, part-time, or relief work. With no after-hours or on-call responsibilities, you can enjoy a healthy balance that fits your lifestyle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ample Support Staff:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;A 2:1 tech-to-doctor ratio, including 3 RVT’s, ensuring you have the resources and respect needed to provide outstanding patient care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comprehensive Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt; Beyond health, dental, vision, and retirement plans, we offer a competitive salary, relocation assistance, a 3.5% 401(k) employer match, generous PTO (plus paid time for CE), annual CE allowance. Licensing, DEA, AVMA PLIT, and membership fees (AVMA, VIN, etc.) are all covered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ongoing Professional Development:&lt;/strong&gt; We encourage lifelong learning and actively support each team member in pursuing their unique interests and professional goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Culture:&lt;/strong&gt; Be part of a supportive, team-oriented environment where your voice is valued. We prioritize staff appreciation and team bonding, hosting fun outings like baseball and hockey games, cookouts, and other get-togethers to celebrate and connect outside of work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Our Hospital:&lt;/strong&gt; Our state-of-the-art facility, built in 2020, was thoughtfully designed to enhance patient care and streamline our team’s workflow. Every detail supports our mission of delivering high-quality veterinary medicine with efficiency, comfort, and compassion. From preventive care to diagnostics, dentistry, and surgery, we provide comprehensive services—without boarding or grooming—so our team can focus on what matters most: medical excellence and client care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equipment &amp;amp; Technology – &lt;/strong&gt;Our hospital is fully equipped with&amp;nbsp;modern, cutting-edge technology, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Digital X-ray &amp;amp; digital dental X-ray&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ultrasound&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-house IDEXX laboratory for rapid diagnostics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;EzyVet paperless PMS system

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maplewood Veterinary Center is seeking a Full-Time Practice Manager.&lt;/strong&gt; We are looking for a people-first leader who is energized by developing teams, building culture, and helping our hospital grow to reach its full potential. This role is ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of leadership and operational excellence, and who takes pride in creating an environment where veterinarians and staff can do their best work to provide animals with the care they deserve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation &amp;amp; Schedule:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary&lt;/strong&gt;: $55,000-75,000 per year determined by the candidate’s skills, experience, and qualifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus&lt;/strong&gt;: Eligible to earn up to 15% in a performance-based annual bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule&lt;/strong&gt;: 9/80 schedule. Enjoy every other Friday off, alternating between four 10-hour days and five 8-hour days each week.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Potential Partnership Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;: High-performing leaders may have the opportunity to participate in equity ownership of the hospital. &lt;em&gt;To be evaluated on annual basis.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Essential Responsibilities:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own hospital growth:&lt;/strong&gt; set the vision, make the decisions, and deliver the best business outcomes for the practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate closely with Doctor co-owner&lt;/strong&gt; on hospital’s growth potential, set goals, remove obstacles, and build a hospital where great medicine and great business go hand in hand.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unlock the potential of your team &lt;/strong&gt;by recruiting top talent, investing in their development, and creating a culture where people do their best work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Champion the client experience&lt;/strong&gt; from first call to follow-up, building loyalty and growing the practice&#39;s reputation in the community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead day-to-day operations:&lt;/strong&gt; staffing, scheduling, inventory, and facilities, so the hospital runs smoothly and efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive financial performance: &lt;/strong&gt;manage P&amp;amp;L, analyze results, and implement strategies that deliver sustainable profitability without compromising the highest quality of care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ensure compliance&lt;/strong&gt; with all applicable laws, regulations, and hospital policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs other related duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in business administration, healthcare management, or a related field is preferred, but candidates with strong relevant skills and experience will also be considered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in a managerial role, preferably in a veterinary or healthcare setting, and knowledge of veterinary procedures, terminology, and industry standards is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with practice management systems is preferred but not required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Leadership and Infrastructure Support:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
